---
description: Run a parallel multi-dimensional review on a GitLab MR
model: gitlab/duo-chat-sonnet-4-6
---

## MR Review Command

Load the `review-mr` skill and execute a full multi-dimensional review of a GitLab merge request.

### Input

The argument is an MR reference in one of these formats:
- `12345` — MR IID, defaults to project `gitlab-org/gitlab`
- `group/project!12345` — Full project path + MR IID
- *(no argument)* — Infer from the current Git branch

### Workflow

1. Parse the argument to extract `project_id` and MR IID
2. If no `project_id` given, default to `gitlab-org/gitlab`
3. If no argument at all, detect the current branch via `git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD` and look up its MR
4. Load the `review-mr` skill for the full orchestration instructions
5. Execute the review workflow: fetch MR data, classify files, dispatch specialized agents in parallel, collect results
6. Present the structured summary to the user

### Notes

- This command dispatches up to 10 specialized review sub-agents in parallel (Security, Database, ClickHouse, Performance, QA, Frontend, Backend, Docs, Analytics, GraphQL)
- Irrelevant dimensions are automatically skipped based on which files changed
- Each agent uses `gitlab/duo-chat-opus-4-6` for deep analysis
- The Security dimension always runs regardless of file types changed
